    <text>
        <body>
            <p>
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>Sepr 10/57</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>94 McDougal St</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dr Sir/</p>
            <p>I send you herewith a Certificate of Deposit<lb/> on the Union Bank of this city for
                $26.50/100<lb/> 50C I deduct for what I have paid for the Parcel;<lb/> making in all
                $25.â€” which the Board of Directors<lb/> of the H. B. Society passed at their 1<hi
                    rend="sup">st</hi> meeting<lb/> after a long recess. Please send a receipt in
                full<lb/> of all Demands to the Treasurer <persName>Mr. J. Heaber</persName>
                <placeName>45 Dey St.</placeName><lb/> or to the Secretary <persName>Mr. A.
                    Lazarus</persName>
                <placeName>15 Day St.</placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">After writing to you last week<lb/> I told
                    <persName>Frankland</persName> who lives at <placeName>10 <del>W 16 Est</del>
                        16<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St</placeName><lb/> to call for the Occident
                    <del>to do</del> at <persName>Mr Seixer's</persName> office<lb/> in
                    <placeName>Bank St.</placeName> according to that gentleman's wish<lb/> but the
                man did not call till last <date>Monday</date><lb/> &amp; he was told that they did
                not take the Parcel<lb/> in &amp; I told him to call at the Express office<lb/> but
                it seems he could not get it, I suppose<lb/> they have sent it back &amp; so the
                matter rests at<lb/> present. <persName>Rev. S. Mr Isaacs</persName> told me
                yesterday<lb/> the same thing as related to him by
                <persName>Frankland</persName><lb/> the man who has carried them and for some
                time.</p>
            <p>I am Dr Sir yours <sic>respectly</sic></p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">M Rubenstein</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
